"title": "4490: ointment",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4490",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A liquid blend of aromatic substances, usually spices, used as a cosmetic and also as a medicinal balm. Lotions were applied to the body to refresh, to improve appearance and to give a pleasing fragrance. Balm, especially from Gilead, was used to soothe pain and to heal wounds.</p>\n<h2>Preparation of ointment</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:31\">JOB 41:31</a></strong> <em>One way of making ointment was to crush solid ingredients and boil them together in olive oil.</em></p>\n<h3>Preparation of the holy anointing oil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:28\">EXO 35:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:6\">EXO 25:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:8\">EXO 35:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:23-Exod30:25\">EXO 30:23–30:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:33\">EXO 30:33</a> <em>The holy anointing oil was to be prepared only by those authorised to do so.</em></p>\n<h3>Ointments made from blended spices</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:14\">2CH 16:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song3:6\">SNG 3:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:56\">LUK 23:56</a></p>\n<h2>Containers for ointment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:20\">ISA 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:7\">MAT 26:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3\">MRK 14:3</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:37\">LUK 7:37</a></p>\n<h2>Uses of ointment</h2>\n<h3>As a cosmetic lotion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:3\">RUT 3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:12\">EST 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:12\">SNG 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:9\">EZK 16:9</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:15\">PSA 104:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:20\">2SA 12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:2\">2SA 14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:8\">ECC 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:3\">DAN 10:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:17\">MAT 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:32\">EXO 30:32</a></p>\n<h3>To anoint the heads of guests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:5\">PSA 23:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps133:2\">PSA 133:2</a> <em>This may reflect the custom of anointing a guest with perfumed ointment which melted and ran down the face and clothes to produce a pleasing fragrance</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:46\">LUK 7:46</a></p>\n<h3>To anoint the dead</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:12\">MAT 26:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:8\">MRK 14:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:7\">JHN 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:2-Gen50:3\">GEN 50:2–50:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:26\">GEN 50:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:1\">MRK 16:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:1\">LUK 24:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:39-John19:40\">JHN 19:39–19:40</a></p>\n<h2>Expensive ointments</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:8-Matt26:9\">MAT 26:8–26:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:4-Mark14:5\">MRK 14:4–14:5</a> <em>(Spike)nard was an expensive import from India.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:17\">PRO 21:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:13-Song4:14\">SNG 4:13–4:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:6\">AMO 6:6</a> <em>The use of expensive ointments was a mark of luxury</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:5\">JHN 12:5</a></p>\n<h2>Ointment used in healing</h2>\n<h3>Oil used to soothe and heal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:6\">ISA 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:21\">PSA 55:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:34\">LUK 10:34</a></p>\n<h3>Medicinal balm</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:22\">JER 8:22</a></strong> <em>Gilead was famous for its healing balsam.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:15\">2CH 28:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:11\">JER 46:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:8\">JER 51:8</a></p>",
